    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** providing the clear anchor of the lineup; his 78.41 efficiency score against Cecconi is the gold standard for our squad, bolstered by an excellent 0.393 xwOBA and a prime #2 hole placement. We are also leaning heavily into our speed-first philosophy with **Trea Turner** (69.16) and **Kyle Schwarber** (68.80) at the top of the order against Colin Rea. While Rea carries a manageable 4.36 xERA, we have discounted **Trea Turner** slightly due to the catcher's elite hold capabilities, though his placement at the leadoff spot ensures he remains a high-floor play. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (61.34) and **Hyeseong Kim** (60.99) round out our aggressive starts; despite being buried in the order, both benefit from favorable park factors that outweigh their low batting positions, keeping them firmly above our 60-point \"Strong\" threshold.\n\nOur most difficult decision of the day involved **Dillon Dingler**, who finished just shy of the cutoff with a 36.01 score. While he possesses the talent to contribute, the negative impact of facing the sharp xERA of Sonny Gray\u2014combined with a punishing 15% platoon penalty\u2014dropped his efficiency well below our 40-point floor. Consequently, we have opted to keep him on the bench to preserve our limited game caps. We are also monitoring several \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Luke Raley**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Victor Scott II**, and **Junior Caminero**. While we are currently projecting their outcomes based on historical slotting, any late-breaking moves down the order could necessitate a re-evaluation of their projected efficiency. Outside of our active roster, **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar** remain sidelined on the IL, while **Zac Veen** continues his development in the minors, leaving us to rely on our active core to maintain our competitive edge in the 5x5 Roto standings.",
